tags: This is mainly in my faves for the Hunter Exam arc, but I will try to keep it there at least until the end of Chimera Ant. Click "More" for my thoughts on each arc.
No point other than an A/V test, but I suppose it has a charm to it.
Nothing like another stupid ONA to add to your list.
anime_title: 3D Onara Gorou ga Dance Dance Dance!!

tags: The first three episodes were better than the last two episodes.

Cool story, but very cluttered. Ash is a GOAT MC, though, but to me, his relationship with Eiji didn't seem as pronounced as a lot of people say it is. Incidentally, I have faith that if there were ever a dub of this, it would be one of the greats.
Although it's not without flaws, it's presented in a way wherein you can easily empathize with the characters - plus a pretty dark tone when dealing with Legoshi's thoughts.

Admittedly hard to compare to the first season given how different they are. Decidedly darker plotlines and a bigger WTF factor to boot. The biggest issue is just how many plotlines are packed into the season. That said, it was still an engaging watch.
Weak story, but pretty cool action and overall environment. Revy is a total babe, too, of course.
The first half is better than the first season, but the Washimine plotline diminished my enjoyment a bit.
Such a great story this was. Deku and All Might are great characters; on the contrary, Bakugo makes me want to punch a wall.

Apparently, this is just supplementary material for the manga of the same name, which may have been a mistake on my part. That said, I won't call this something it's not. Good music, but terrible dubbing and sound design.

The biggest issue with this was how some episodes were awesome and others made me feel nothing. On the contrary, this has great character dynamics, amazing music, and a generally cool, well-constructed atmosphere.
Just a throwaway, but not bad by any means.
While the show is not always laugh-out-loud worthy and the jokes occasionally get old, it's still an enjoyable watch.
My thoughts are pretty much the same as those on the first season.
Decent anime with some stupid moments, sexy moments, and feel-good moments. A bit disappointing, though.
This being my first anime, I will always love it. There are lots of crazy twists here, some better than others. Favorite arc is Singapore Sky. Overall a great watch.

Love these characters; Hinata and Kageyama are great characters, and the third-years are very admirable - the kind of people I'd wanna be like. The volleyball and teamwork themes are admittedly lost on me, but I still love this.
A good, casual look at the Nekoma team (with special guests Karasuno).
Parts 1 and 2 are about equal to me, though Part 2 had a great ending. Very cheesy, sure, but still enjoyable.

Not as good as Parts 1 and 2. The big problem with this (besides the length) is just how much the series relies on deus ex machinas, some of which are plain outrageous. One thing I will say, though, is that Jotaro is my favorite JoJo so far.
anime_title: JoJo no Kimyou na Bouken Part 3: Stardust Crusaders

tags: The stands are coming even harder than before. That said, despite a few great episodes (including the last 9), this was about on par with Season 1. On the plus side, the 2-part episodes forced me to power through more quickly.
anime_title: JoJo no Kimyou na Bouken Part 3: Stardust Crusaders 2nd Season
anime_title_eng: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure: Stardust Crusaders - Battle in Egypt

tags: My favorite part of JoJo thus far. Not perfect, but there are some excellent episodes along with a great cast and overall style.
anime_title: JoJo no Kimyou na Bouken Part 4: Diamond wa Kudakenai
anime_title_eng: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure: Diamond is Unbreakable

tags: A few very good episodes at the beginning and end, but the majority of it suffers from bad pacing - you can barely see the girls evolve as musicians. Plus, a lot of the characters tended to get on my nerves a bit.
Although the stories were a bit ridiculous, this was a very good OVA series that I would love to see more of down the road.

I had a very basic understanding of the story, but not much further than that. However, Odokawa is great, and the voice acting is really good, too. Not to mention, the ending was insane. Overall, though, this was quite a disappointment.
Decent enough, but the last arc was really good. This show had tons of great turns.
Cool animation and action sequences, but a bit of a weak story. The last few episodes were pretty cool, though.
Well-made, but it was a bit style-over-substance to me. Not to mention, the ending was a bit anti-climactic. Watched with MAL users simone_eatsdirt and mwinner.
No point, but a nice little test.

This series is by no means perfect, and some themes are a bit lost on me, but it's still got great character dynamics and killer music. Might be my favorite Watanabe show despite it not being his creation.
I think this is better than Cowboy Bebop by a hair. Borrows Bebop's character dynamics perfectly.
There are some bits I'm not a huge fan of, but it's still alright, and it has a good deal of fantastic moments. Could swing between 6 and 7.
Just ridiculous. Actually made me a little sick.
Doesn't feel much like an anime. Nothing really too inventive, but still good - especially the last arc. Watched with MAL users simone_eatsdirt and mwinner (partly).
May be a bit predictable at times, but the presentation is excellent.
It'll probably be a long time before I come back to this.
Wasn't too impressed by this one, but I'll probably try again.
